1.3 Introduction to functions

oddcount <- function(x){
  k <- 0
  for (n in x) {
    if (n %% 2 == 1) 
      k <- k + 1
  }
  return(k)
}
oddcount(c(1, 3, 5))
## [1] 3
oddcount(c(0, 1, 2, 3, 7, 9))
## [1] 4

1.3.1 scope of variable

Global variable

f <- function(x) return(x + y)  # warning: no symbol names y in scope
y <- 3
f(5)
## [1] 8

1.3.2 Default arguments

g <- function(x, y=2, z=3) return(x * y * z)
g(x = 5)
## [1] 30
